  "type": "mcq",
  "stimulus": null,
  "stem": "<p>If <math><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> is a solution to the system <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math> and <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, which of the following could be the ordered pair?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>(0, 0)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>(-1, 2)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p>(1, -2)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p>(3, 6)</p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "d"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Substituting <math><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math> for <em>y</em> in the second equation yields <math><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, or <math><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Factoring gives <math><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, so <em>x</em> = 3 or <em>x</em> = -1. When <em>x</em> = 3, <em>y</em> = 2(3) = 6, giving (3, 6).</p><p>Choices A, B, and C are incorrect.</p>",
